  "prompt": "How do l see who viewed my videos on Instagram?",
  "response": "Unfortunately, Instagram does not provide a direct feature to see exactly who has viewed your videos. Here's what you can see:\n\n1. For Instagram Stories:\n- You can see the number of views\n- By tapping \"Seen by\" you can view a list of accounts that have viewed your story\n- This list is only available for 24 hours after posting the story\n\n2. For IGTV and Reels:\n- You can see the total view count\n- You cannot see individual viewer names\n\n3. For Regular Feed Posts (videos/photos):\n- You can see the total number of views and likes\n- You cannot see who specifically viewed the post\n\nIf you want to track engagement, you can:\n- Check your post's insights (if you have a business or creator account)\n- Look at comments and likes to see who interacted with your content\n- Use Instagram's built-in analytics for more detailed information about your posts' performance\n\nThird-party apps claiming to show who viewed your profile or videos are generally not reliable and may compromise your account security.",
